data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"parts": [{"text": "**Refining Joke Criteria**\n\nI'm now focusing on what constitutes a \"better\" joke. Beyond simple puns, I'm aiming for cleverness and wordplay, such as double meanings and setups leading to unexpected punchlines. I'm also considering broader relatability as a key factor.\n\n\n","thought": true}],"role": "model"},"index": 0}],"usageMetadata": {"promptTokenCount": 634,"totalTokenCount": 699,"promptTokensDetails": [{"modality": "TEXT","tokenCount": 634}],"thoughtsTokenCount": 65,"serviceTier": "standard"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.5-flash","responseId": "sOz_aY-pB62M_PUPt9nG0AU"}

data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"parts": [{"text": "**Developing Humor Targets**\n\nI'm now focusing on defining \"better\" jokes. I'm prioritizing clever wordplay beyond simple puns, particularly double meanings and unexpected punchlines. Relatability and surprise are key components. I'm also planning to test out jokes based on observational humor, abstract concepts, or classic one-liner formats. I'm aiming for setups with misdirection leading to a punchline twist.\n\n\n","thought": true}],"role": "model"},"index": 0}],"usageMetadata": {"promptTokenCount": 634,"totalTokenCount": 995,"promptTokensDetails": [{"modality": "TEXT","tokenCount": 634}],"thoughtsTokenCount": 361,"serviceTier": "standard"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.5-flash","responseId": "sOz_aY-pB62M_PUPt9nG0AU"}

data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"parts": [{"text": "**Analyzing Joke Effectiveness**\n\nI've been contrasting a few recent jokes. The \"paranoia\" library joke creates a quick narrative and a surprising punchline through misdirection. The \"spider\" joke, by contrast, relies on a literal interpretation leading to absurdity in a relatable situation. The spider joke seems a better fit for a humorous extreme, though both are concise. I'm aiming for more elaborate setups with a humorous twist to improve the overall joke.\n\n\n","thought": true}],"role": "model"},"index": 0}],"usageMetadata": {"promptTokenCount": 634,"totalTokenCount": 1241,"promptTokensDetails": [{"modality": "TEXT","tokenCount": 634}],"thoughtsTokenCount": 607,"serviceTier": "standard"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.5-flash","responseId": "sOz_aY-pB62M_PUPt9nG0AU"}

data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"parts": [{"text": "**Evaluating Joke Formats**\n\nI've been contrasting a few recent jokes. The \"paranoia\" library joke creates a quick narrative and a surprising punchline through misdirection. The \"spider\" joke, by contrast, relies on a literal interpretation leading to absurdity in a relatable situation. The spider joke seems a better fit for a humorous extreme, though both are concise. I'm aiming for more elaborate setups with a humorous twist to improve the overall joke.\n\nI've decided to analyze a couple of different jokes. I'm prioritizing the spider joke because it has an involved setup and a surprising, absurd twist. The spider joke, \"My wife told me to take the spider out instead of killing it. So I took it to a nice restaurant, had a few drinks, and told it I wanted to see other people,\" has relatable domestic situation, misdirection and punchline. The punchline is absurd and literal. The goal is to move beyond simple pun, and this helps!\n\n\n","thought": true}],"role": "model"},"index": 0}],"usageMetadata": {"promptTokenCount": 634,"totalTokenCount": 1486,"promptTokensDetails": [{"modality": "TEXT","tokenCount": 634}],"thoughtsTokenCount": 852,"serviceTier": "standard"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.5-flash","responseId": "sOz_aY-pB62M_PUPt9nG0AU"}

data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"parts": [{"text": "**Prioritizing Setup Refinement**\n\nNow I'm focusing on crafting jokes with more involved setups to create greater narrative and humorous punchlines. I've chosen to analyze the \"spider\" joke. It showcases a domestic situation, misdirection, and an absurd literal punchline. The goal now is to consistently create jokes with unexpected twists, moving beyond simple puns for a \"better\" result.\n\n\n","thought": true}],"role": "model"},"index": 0}],"usageMetadata": {"promptTokenCount": 634,"totalTokenCount": 1506,"promptTokensDetails": [{"modality": "TEXT","tokenCount": 634}],"thoughtsTokenCount": 872,"serviceTier": "standard"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.5-flash","responseId": "sOz_aY-pB62M_PUPt9nG0AU"}

